Cell.Data: Gears with red background on the name means that the game gives you limited ammount of this specific item. I don’t recommend you to sell them (see next note) as once you have sell them, they are gone forever.
The third column clarifies if the item can be sold on the store. If it is “N” with an orange background, means that the game doesn’t allows you to sell it.
I left the second column empty so you can track there the number os items of that specific Gear you have.
Fourth column indicates if the Gear can be Upgraded. An “U” means that it can be upgraded. If there is a “N” with a orange background, as before, means that you can’t upgrade said Gear.
Fifth column tells you if you can change Color. Again, a C means yes (color) and a “N” with orange backgound is a no.

You can only obtain 1 item per limited Gear. Exception are “Karate Gloves”, “Blanka-Chan Costume”, “ENDACTUS” & “Bikini Top” with 2 per each. “Haggar T-Shirt” can be obtained 5 times. You obtain it by fighting different Andore and each one has a different condition. If you want to obtain 5 (to have all different color variants) you have only one chance per Andore, but remember that you can escape or lose the fight in order to rematch. If you win without obtaining it, it is gone forever.

Regarding “Sumo Yukata”, you obtain it on a certain fight in the last in-game tournament. I THINK that you can “Give Up” after this combat, restart the tournament, and obtain this item again, but I can’t confirm/deny it. Can you? ;)
